long_desc.thetext:
In GMT-UMLX project the eqvtoperational and eimperativeocl metamodels are needed to complete the set of EQVT languages.
A patch will be included, which will affect the "org.eclipse.gmt.umlx.eqvt" project and it will contain the following features: - eqvtoperational.ecore and eimperative.ecore metamodel files. - the corresponding configured .genmodel files - the corresponding java packages generated by EMF. - The implementation of XMIResourceAdapterFactory and MappingMetaData for both metamodels. - the modified MANIFEST.MF (to export the generated packages). - the modified plugin.xml (to use the EMF "generated_package" extension point and Model Registry "model_content" extension point).
Regards, Adolfo.

Created attachment 86700 Proposed patch
The patch which provides the enhancement
Cheers !!!

Patch applied quite easily; looks promising. I wrote a dummy unit test to map backwards and forward between QVTo and EQVTo, which provokes meta-data validation. ----- A number of easily fixed problems show up with respect to the latest QVT.
UnpackExp.variable is now UnpackExp.targetVariable
MappingOperation.isBlackbox has moved to ImperativeOperation.isBlackbox
ContextualProperty.initExpression has been added
OperationalTransformation.ownedVariable has moved to Module.ownedVariable
MappingParameter.refinedDomain is now MappingParameter.referredDomain
DictLiteralExp.part was incorrectly declared ordered in SmartQVT
VariableInitExp.referredVariable is now composed ------ Please advise on the following two. I would prefer to change EQVT.
UnpackExp.targetVariable is ordered in QVT, !ordered in EQVT.
ImperativeIterateExp.target is composed in QVT, !composed in EQVT. ------
PrimitiveTypeOM and PredefinedTypeOM are not defined in QVT so it is not obvious how to convert the EQVT to QVT.
Are they really necessary?
If they're just renames, preserve the QVT names.
If they're debatable bug fixes, then we can add a QVTOperationalPlus similar to QVTCorePlus.
If they're unarguable bug fixes, then we can modify QVTOperational.

Hi Ed,
Some comments below, about the corrections (Thx for them, my last revision was not as exhaustive as it should be ;). The incongruities between the diagram and text of the abstract syntax doesn't help :( )...
(In reply to comment #2) > Patch applied quite easily; looks promising. I wrote a dummy unit test to map > backwards and forward between QVTo and EQVTo, which provokes meta-data > validation. > ----- > A number of easily fixed problems show up with respect to the latest QVT. > > UnpackExp.variable is now UnpackExp.targetVariable
Right.
> MappingOperation.isBlackbox has moved to ImperativeOperation.isBlackbox
Right.
> ContextualProperty.initExpression has been added
Right. Another correction: Change overriden association cardinality to [0..1].
> OperationalTransformation.ownedVariable has moved to Module.ownedVariable
Right.
> MappingParameter.refinedDomain is now MappingParameter.referredDomain
Well. This is a new problem derived from the incongruity among the diagram and the text. Generally the diagram usually is the "correct" one. In this case the referredDomain appears in the text. By the way, it seems that referredDomain should be a better name for the association.
> DictLiteralExp.part was incorrectly declared ordered in SmartQVT
Right.
> VariableInitExp.referredVariable is now composed
Right. It was in the ecore metamodel, was'nt it ? > ------ > Please advise on the following two. I would prefer to change EQVT. > > UnpackExp.targetVariable is ordered in QVT, !ordered in EQVT.
Yes it should be ordered in the EQVT.
> ImperativeIterateExp.target is composed in QVT, !composed in EQVT.
Well. We have a new incongruity. In the diagram appears as composed, in the text does'nt. I think that it should not be composed. The ImperativeIterateExp target variable generally refers to an Iterator variable (the later is part of OCL-LoopExp).
> ------ > > PrimitiveTypeOM and PredefinedTypeOM are not defined in QVT so it is not > obvious how to convert the EQVT to QVT. > > Are they really necessary?
Well they are personal additions, that could be removed in the future when the QVTo Standard Library is resolved.
We have some QVTo Types which are EClasses (ModelType, OperationalTransformation), so I have added the specified EOperations at M2 level, and i have made that EClasses to inheritance PredefinedType (from OCL). With this way (and implementing the oclOperations method for ModelTypeImpl and OperationalTransformationImpl) the parser can succesfully lookup the operations.
In the future, when we have a well-built QVTo Std Lib. The parser will have to lookup operations for that types, in the QVTo Std Lib.
I'll have to workaround this.
> If they're just renames, preserve the QVT names. > > If they're debatable bug fixes, then we can add a QVTOperationalPlus similar to > QVTCorePlus. > > If they're unarguable bug fixes, then we can modify QVTOperational. >
Yes they are out-of-specification so they should not be in the QVTo Ecore. They are temporary implementation for my parser.
About the incongruities among the text and the diagrams of the abstract syntax. I have sent and issue of one of them. If it is accepted, i'll start to send a lot of them that i have written down.
Cheers !!!!

> Another correction: Change ContextualProperty.overriden association cardinality > to [0..1].
There seems to be a case for each option. My QVT zips are 1, though 0..1 on the diagram.
The text seems to suggest that an override is necessary.
Is a ContextualProperty without an override meaningful?

(In reply to comment #4) > > Another correction: Change ContextualProperty.overriden association cardinality > > to [0..1]. > > There seems to be a case for each option. My QVT zips are 1, though 0..1 on the > diagram. > > The text seems to suggest that an override is necessary. > > Is a ContextualProperty without an override meaningful? >
Yes it is... It is the more usual. Contextual properties are used to make extensions of classes (meta) of a defined metamodel. Why do i need to override a property if i just want to add a new property to a metaclass inside the transformation?.
In my point of view, when executing a transformation we could be interested in extending a metaclass with a contextual property with the following purposes:
1. override another property: In order to specify or tight the type of a already existing property. 2. without overriding: In order to simply add a new property.
In conclusion: I think that the diagram is right, and the text is wrong ;P
P.D: Should i re-send a new patch with the related changes? P.D2: Could i have the unit test that you mentioned ? I would like to have a look ;P

No need to re-send. I can easily do/have done the changes. If you resent, I would just have to re-implement the eefactoring to support per-package non-inherited MappingMetaData.
The JUnit test will be in the ...eqvto.tests plug-in. You can look at the eqvtc.tests or eqvtr.tests plugins to see the principles.
I hope to complete the refactoring of MappingMetaData very shortly. It's taking longer than I expected and I'm not getting as much time as I'd like.

Contribution now committed to CVS together with a redesign of MappingMetaData to eliminate the inheritance relationships that would have prevented QVTo working. Note that the MappingMetaData classes have been renamed to use the naming of the non-Ecore package.
CVS should be coherent with respect to M4 for all UMLX plugins packages except *.diagram. NB make sure you refresh the model registry projects too except *.oaw which is very optional.
Now that all the required M4s are available, I'll try to get an EcoreTools alignment going and provide a complete M4 zip.

Created attachment 97667 Contributed Test Case
The attached patch, provides a complete example of a QVTo model, with a test case to check the QVToMetaDataMapping.

The attached patch runs incredibly slowly because it has proxy references to http://www.eclipse.org/uml2/2.1.0/UML which is not a registered model and so provokes an Internet access failure for each proxy. EMF does not cache URI failures so each proxy results in an independent Internet access failure.
[The org.eclipse.gmt.umlx.alien.mapping.MappingUtils.isGeneric method is triggering the proxy resolution and failing to make the resolution failure evident. The need to resolve classifiers to examine their type parameters should be viewed, and proxy resolution failure propagated.]
It is not a good idea to introduce an additional plugin dependency for a basic test, so please supply a test model that includes its own metamodels.
Testing of UML2 models is perhaps something for an other test plug-in.
